2 bombs... one on Nagasaki and one on Hiroshima. Two of the largest (note, not THE largest) wholesale slaughtering of civilian populations.  After the second bomb the government of Japan surrendered the next day not wishing to see more hundreds of thousands of civilians turned into a piles of ash and glass.  While both were terrifying and morally questionable.  Most every historian agrees that those bombs probably saved more lives in the long run than the invasion of Japan would have cost in either Japanese or American lives.  More than a few Japanese from that era agreed that it was probably the best decision for both sides.<br>
