There's a few things you need to wake up to about warfare.  It's not pretty and it sure as hell isn't perfect.  Laser guided bombs, GPS guided cruise missiles and such are pretty new to the war arena.  The numbers are in on those laser guided bombs... only about 40% actually hit their intended targets.  Where do you think the rest go?  That's right... right into the neighboorhoods surrounding those factories where all the workers for that plant live.  Housing developers don't take military strikes into consideration when building those neighboorhoods.  They build them as close to the factories as they are allowed to as a matter of day to day convenience for those workers and those workers are going to flat out die when the shit starts hitting the fan.  It's a sad thing but it's a flat out fact of war and of life.  Yes, it would be nice if all factories were built 50 miles away from all housing.  Yes, it would be nice if the pilots had the luxury of cruising to ten feet off the ground so they could hit their targets more accurately... however, they are more concerened with getting home alive to their own families which means dropping those bombs from thousands of feet in the air.  They could really give a rat's ass about what you think of their targeting ability back in the confort of your own home while their ass is the one on the line dodging SAMs and trying to accomplish their mission.<br>
<br>
I know what you're saying about trying to target military first and such but when you're a religious zealot fighting what you perceive as the devil's kingdom on earth you're going to use whatever means at your disposal to strike at the heart of it.  I imagine UBL feels very justified in wasting the lives of the few innocents on those airplanes in order to bring about what he was sure would be a stake through the heart of the devil's empire.  All governemts at some time or another have considered it a fiar trade off of a few innocent lives to achieve what they believed to be the greater good.  UBL doesn't have an army.  No army on earth is foolish enough launch a frontal assault on the US.  They know they're going to lose.  So they have to try whatever other means are at their disposal.  And they too, are going to give a rat's ass about you think of their morality when they believe beyond any doubt that they are fighting by God's word.<br>
<br>
The response to that I'm afraid is going to be a lot more immoral acts in order to properly defend against those kinds of tactics for the greater good.<br>
